data.enText: bad behaviour (especially of children) that is annoying but does not cause any serious damage or harm
Those children are always getting into mischief .
I try to keep out of mischief .

data.chText: 楼上很安静。他们一定在搞什么恶作剧。
data.enText: It's very quiet upstairs; they must be up to some mischief !
the wish or tendency to behave or play in a way that causes trouble

data.chText: 她眼睛里满是使坏的神情。
data.enText: Her eyes were full of mischief.
harm or injury that is done to sb or to their reputation

data.chText: 这一事件造成了严重的政治危害。
data.enText: The incident caused a great deal of political mischief.

data.chText: 看你那是怎么用剪刀啊——你会伤着自己的！
data.enText: Watch how you use those scissors─you could do yourself a mischief!
to do or say sth deliberately to upset other people, or cause trouble between them

data.chText: 看你那是怎么用剪刀啊——你会伤着自己的！
data.enText: Watch how you use those scissors─you could do yourself a mischief!
to do or say sth deliberately to upset other people, or cause trouble between them

tr: reckless or malicious behavior that causes discomfort or annoyance in others
the quality or nature of being harmful or evil

value.def: Mischief is playing harmless tricks on people or doing things you are not supposed to do. It can also refer to the desire to do this.

example.ex: The little lad was a real handful. He was always up to mischief...
example.tran: 这个小家伙真是难管教，他总是搞恶作剧。

example.ex: Boys at that age should be able to explore and go off on their own, go on bike rides, get into mischief...
example.tran: 那个年龄的男孩应该可以自己出去闯，也可以骑车出游，还可以调皮捣蛋。

example.ex: His eyes were full of  mischief.

value.tran: 恶作剧;淘气;使坏的念头

value.def: Mischief is behaviour that is intended to cause trouble for people. It can also refer to the trouble that is caused.

example.ex: The more sinister explanation is that he is about to make mischief in the Middle East again...
example.tran: 更为险恶的解释是，他准备再次在中东地区制造事端。

example.ex: They withdrew their support after the President described the conference as a platform to cause political mischief.
example.tran: 在总统称这次大会是在制造政治事端之后，他们便撤回了对这次会议的支持。

value.tran: 惹麻烦之事;引起问题的行为；损害;麻烦
